sql:
SELECT name
FROM medicines
WHERE medicine_id IN (0, 1);

external_knowledge:
- High demand is defined as a total demand greater than 100 units;
- Inventory refers to the total quantity of the medicine in stock;
- Manufacturer details include the name, address, contact email, phone number, and website of the manufacturer;
- Batch details include the batch number, expiration date, and quantity of the batch;
- Cumulative demand is the total demand for a medicine over time, calculated by summing the demand for each demand entry.

sql:
